<paragraph base="F55756218" id="IFRS17_BC406"><paranum>BC406</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="BC406"/></prolog><body><bodydiv base="IFRS2020-3">             <p id="IFRS17_P6567">However, because IFRS 17 was developed in the context of <xref href="../ifrs14/IFRS15_TOC.dita#IFRS15_TOC0001/IFRS15_TOC0001_V2">IFRS 15</xref>                 and <xref href="../ifrs09/IFRS09_TOC.dita#IFRS09_TOC0001/IFRS09_TOC0001_V1">IFRS 9</xref>, and given the extent of changes the Board expects will be needed                 to apply IFRS 17, the Board concluded that an entity should be permitted to apply                 IFRS 17 only when it also applies IFRS 15 and IFRS 9.<xref type="fn" keyref="footnotes/IFRS17_BC406_FN0001"/></p>         </bodydiv></body></paragraph>